content: The DeFi event was a whirlwind of ideas and connections. Got some solid feedback on our AI model, and an investor hinted at funding if we can show more consistent results. The pressure's on!
Our smart contract passed another audit round. No vulnerabilities this time, but the real test is trading with real money. We’re prepping for the next phase, fingers crossed.

Struggled with the ensemble methods, but we're getting there. The model's now at 65% accuracy. Every percentage point feels like a victory. Also, had a date night, and it was nice to think about something other than trading for a change.
Just finished analyzing our past trading losses. It’s not just about the numbers; it’s about understanding the market’s mood swings. Documenting these insights to refine our risk management.
Met with my trading buddy again. He’s got this idea about using market sentiment analysis to boost our predictions. It’s a stretch, but I’m intrigued. Time to expand our data sources.
The AI model's now flirting with 68% accuracy. It's like watching a plant grow; slow but rewarding. Also, had a family dinner, and it was grounding to share some of my work-life balance struggles.
Our smart contract is now live with real trading data. It's thrilling and terrifying. The markets are unpredictable, but our model's holding up, for now.
Spent the last few days diving into advanced ML techniques. Tried out a new neural network architecture, and the results are promising. Maybe this is the breakthrough we need.
Had a setback; the model dropped to 64% accuracy after a market shift. But setbacks are just setups for comebacks, right? Time to recalibrate and learn from this.
Just got off a call with a potential investor. They're interested in our project but want to see a demo with live trading data. It’s a big ask, but we're ready to show what we've got.
The city skyline from my window reminds me of the endless possibilities. We're integrating market sentiment analysis now, and the model’s accuracy is climbing again. Slow progress is still progress.
Our smart contract executed its first trade based on AI predictions. It was a small win, but a win nonetheless. Every trade is a learning opportunity, and we're documenting everything.

Just got the latest feedback from our investor. They're impressed, but want us to focus on scalability. It's time to think bigger, not just about the model but how it fits into the larger DeFi ecosystem.
